summary: This document appears to be a consent form from Deutsche Asset & Wealth Management regarding the electronic delivery of materials and communications. It outlines the terms under which clients can receive documents electronically and the responsibilities of both the client and the firm. The document emphasizes the importance of providing accurate contact information and the ability to revoke consent at any time.
keyFacts: The document is a consent form for electronic delivery of materials from Deutsche Asset & Wealth Management.
Clients must provide accurate email addresses and notify the firm of any changes to their contact information.
The consent can be revoked at any time by the client.
The document includes legal disclaimers regarding the availability of certain offerings only to clients outside the United States.
There are references to various Deutsche Bank entities involved in the delivery of materials.
